<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<project name="99MarchMadness" themePath="default" format="1.4">
<forms>
<form name="Sw16EntryScreen" startPoint="true" themePath="default" process="EntryProcess">
<items>
<text label="T1"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">This makes the NCAA men's basketball tournament bracket into a Tawala project. This version includes only the teams still playing after the first weekend.</font></paragraph></text>
<text label="T2"><paragraph indent="0" align="left">Instructions and Scoring:</paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left">Players must predict the winner of each of the 15 games in the NCAA men's basketball tournament. Points are scored on the basis of 1 point for each favorite team correctly predicted to win and 2 points for each underdog correctly favored to win. (The underdog will have the higher numbered seed.)</paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left">Extra points are awarded for correctly predicting the champion as follows:</paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left">If the eventual champion is a No. 1 seed, earn 1 extra point</paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left">If the eventual champion is seeded 2, 3, or 4, earn 2 extra points.</paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left">If the eventual champion is seeded higher than 4, earn 3 extra points.</paragraph></text>
<fib label="Q1"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><font face="Arial" size="180" color="000000">Enter a user name. Be sure to keep track of it, because you'll need it to check back on your score.

Please note: It is perfectly permissable to make more than one set of bracket predictions. But you must use a separate user name for each set.

 </font><blank label="a" length="28" required="true" alternateLabel="UserName"/></paragraph></fib>
<text label="T3"><paragraph indent="0" align="left">Once the Tawala executable can pass the date to the project, question 2 will morph into a date check. If the date is before the closing for predictions, the player would be sent to the RoundOf64Screen Form (in this example, the Sweet16Screen Form). If the date is after the closing, the player would be sent directly to the ScoreIt Form.</paragraph></text>
<mc label="Q2" onlyone="true" required="true"><question><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">What do you want to do?</font></paragraph></question><choice label="a"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">Make my bracket projections.</font></paragraph></choice><choice label="b"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">Check the Leaderboard</font></paragraph></choice></mc>
</items>
</form>
<form name="Sweet16Form" startPoint="false" themePath="default" process="Sweet16Process">
<items>
<text label="T1"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">Sweet 16 predictions.</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">(Numbers before the school's name represent their seeding in the bracket. Each quarter of the bracket is seeded separately, which explains why there are four teams seeded No. 1. When teams with the same seed play each other, which will only happen in the semifinals or finals, only 1 point is awarded for accurately predicting the winner.)</font></paragraph></text>
<mc label="Q1" onlyone="true" required="true"><question><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">Who wins Game 1?</font></paragraph></question><choice label="a"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">1. Duke</font></paragraph></choice><choice label="b"><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Arial" size="200" color="000000">4. LSU</font></paragraph></choice></mc>
