<document name="Help">
<xmlData>
<paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000"><b>Preventing duplicate user names:</b></font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">The Process UserTest shows how to check for properly registered users for the contest. When applied to a broad audience, UserNames should be dupe-checked to prevent duplicates.</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000"><b>Scoring:</b></font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">(from Sw16EntryForm):</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Any other scoring mechanism can be substituted. A popular one is an arithmetic progression that rewards players for accuracy in the later rounds of the tournament. It goes like this:</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Round of 64: 1 point for predicting a favorite that wins, 2 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Round of 32: 2 points for predicting a favorite that wins, 3 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Sweet 16: 3 points for predicting a favorite that wins, 4 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Elite8: 4 points or predicting a favorite that wins, 5 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Final4: 5 points for a favorite that wins, 6 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Championship game: 6 points for a favorite that wins, 7 points for an underdog</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000"><b>Setting up the brackets:</b></font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Each round needs to be in a separate Form. Using this project as a template, start with the RoundOf64, progress to the RoundOf32 and pick up with the Sweet16. The Process for the RoundOf64 Form uses SET commands to identify the teams playing and collects the player's choices. Subsequent Processes use variables from the RoundOf64 Process to record playr's choices. Each Form subsequent to the initial RoundOf64 Form will use those SET commands to show the player his choices from the previous round and ask him to predict the winners of the round in question.</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">FinalScoreForm provides a separate access to the scoring element. It should be substituted for access to the Sw16EntryScreen, once entries are closed. This sceen will be unnecessary once the executable passes date stamps to the project. The Process for this Form conducts a user test to make sure that the user is a registered player, then shows the Leaderboard. If not, the Document Oops is displayed.</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000"><b>The Leaderboard:</b></font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Once entries are closed, data is exported from the FinalsForm section of the project on theTawala server to a spreadsheet. A new column, "Score" is inserted into the spreadsheet to the right of the UserName. This spreadsheet calculates player scores and serves as the source of data for the Leaderboard. Scoring cells in the spreadsheet are added as each game is played. The form of the cell's calculation is</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">=IF(cellX,Y="seed_team",S,0)</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">where cell X,Y is the location of the cell containing the original prediction</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">"seed_team" is the actual seed and school name, such as 1. Duke</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">and S equals the score assigned to that particular correct prediction and will vary with the scoring algorithm chosen. </font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">The columns UserName and Score are copied and pasted into the Leaderboard document. A sample Leaderboard document was included, but there are infinite variations on the theme.</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">The spreadsheet used during play testing is available upon request. E-mail:</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">softalk@sbcglobal.net</font></paragraph>
</xmlData>
<htmlData>
<![CDATA[<p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000"><b>Preventing duplicate user names:</b></span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">The Process UserTest shows how to check for properly registered users for the contest. When applied to a broad audience, UserNames should be dupe-checked to prevent duplicates.</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000"><b>Scoring:</b></span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">(from Sw16EntryForm):</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Any other scoring mechanism can be substituted. A popular one is an arithmetic progression that rewards players for accuracy in the later rounds of the tournament. It goes like this:</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Round of 64: 1 point for predicting a favorite that wins, 2 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Round of 32: 2 points for predicting a favorite that wins, 3 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Sweet 16: 3 points for predicting a favorite that wins, 4 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Elite8: 4 points or predicting a favorite that wins, 5 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Final4: 5 points for a favorite that wins, 6 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Championship game: 6 points for a favorite that wins, 7 points for an underdog</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000"><b>Setting up the brackets:</b></span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Each round needs to be in a separate Form. Using this project as a template, start with the RoundOf64, progress to the RoundOf32 and pick up with the Sweet16. The Process for the RoundOf64 Form uses SET commands to identify the teams playing and collects the player's choices. Subsequent Processes use variables from the RoundOf64 Process to record playr's choices. Each Form subsequent to the initial RoundOf64 Form will use those SET commands to show the player his choices from the previous round and ask him to predict the winners of the round in question.</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">FinalScoreForm provides a separate access to the scoring element. It should be substituted for access to the Sw16EntryScreen, once entries are closed. This sceen will be unnecessary once the executable passes date stamps to the project. The Process for this Form conducts a user test to make sure that the user is a registered player, then shows the Leaderboard. If not, the Document Oops is displayed.</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000"><b>The Leaderboard:</b></span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">Once entries are closed, data is exported from the FinalsForm section of the project on theTawala server to a spreadsheet. A new column, "Score" is inserted into the spreadsheet to the right of the UserName. This spreadsheet calculates player scores and serves as the source of data for the Leaderboard. Scoring cells in the spreadsheet are added as each game is played. The form of the cell's calculation is</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">=IF(cellX,Y="seed_team",S,0)</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">where cell X,Y is the location of the cell containing the original prediction</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">"seed_team" is the actual seed and school name, such as 1. Duke</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">and S equals the score assigned to that particular correct prediction and will vary with the scoring algorithm chosen. </span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">The columns UserName and Score are copied and pasted into the Leaderboard document. A sample Leaderboard document was included, but there are infinite variations on the theme.</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">The spreadsheet used during play testing is available upon request. E-mail:</span></p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-left:0pt" align="left"><span style="font-family:'Garamond';font-size:12pt;color:#000000">softalk@sbcglobal.net</span></p>]]>
</htmlData>
</document>
<document name="YourPicks">
<xmlData>
<paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Good going, </font><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000"><field name="Sw16EntryScreen:UserName"/></font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions><font face="Garamond" size="240" color="000000">Here is a recap of your picks:</font></paragraph><paragraph indent="0" align="left"><tabPositions><tabStop position="720"/><tabStop position="1440"/><tabStop position="2160"/><tabStop position="2880"/><tabStop position="3600"/><tabStop position="4320"/><tabStop position="5040"/><tabStop position="5760"/><tabStop position="6480"/><tabStop position="7200"/><tabStop position="7920"/><tabStop position="8640"/><tabStop position="9360"/><tabStop position="10080"/></tabPositions></par